Constructor Detail

MaximumEntropyClassifier.Factory

public MaximumEntropyClassifier.Factory(double sigma,
                                        int iterations,
                                        FeatureExtractor<I,F> featureExtractor)
Sigma controls the variance on the prior / penalty term. 1.0 is a reasonable value for large problems, bigger sigma means LESS smoothing. Zero sigma is a special indicator that no smoothing is to be done.

Iterations determines the maximum number of iterations the optimization code can take before stopping.
